# FreeCRM Deployment

- Host: `test.itconnect.pl`, root `/opt/freecrm`, manage via `docker compose`.
- SSH: `bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl`.
- HTTPS: Let's Encrypt via Cloudflare DNS (`certbot/dns-cloudflare`, creds in `docker/nginx/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini`). Nginx reads `docker/nginx/certs/{host}.{fullchain,privkey}.pem` only — after issue/renew, copy from `letsencrypt/live/` (see `renewal/*.conf`). Privkeys: `640`, group `www-data` (nginx uid 33).
- Hostnames: `test.itconnect.pl` on this server; `dev.itconnect.pl` in the same `default.conf` for local Docker.
- Services: `web`, `app`, `cron`, `db`.
- Cron: `docker compose up -d cron` runs `cron/vtigercron.php` every minute via supercronic; log at `cache/logs/cron.log`.
- Storage: `/opt/freecrm/storage` (copied from `10.0.0.220:/var/www/yetiforce/storage`).
- Migration backups: `/opt/freecrm/_migration`; local rollback dump at `tmp/migration-20260511-134258/`.

## TLS (issue / renew)

From repo root; replace `HOST` (`dev.itconnect.pl` or `test.itconnect.pl`):

```bash
docker run --rm \
  -v "$PWD/docker/nginx/letsencrypt:/etc/letsencrypt" \
  -v "$PWD/docker/nginx/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini:/etc/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini:ro" \
  certbot/dns-cloudflare certonly --dns-cloudflare \
  --dns-cloudflare-credentials /etc/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini \
  --dns-cloudflare-propagation-seconds 60 \
  -d HOST --key-type ecdsa --non-interactive --agree-tos --register-unsafely-without-email

sudo cp docker/nginx/letsencrypt/live/HOST/fullchain.pem docker/nginx/certs/HOST.fullchain.pem
sudo cp docker/nginx/letsencrypt/live/HOST/privkey.pem docker/nginx/certs/HOST.privkey.pem
sudo chgrp www-data docker/nginx/certs/HOST.privkey.pem && sudo chmod 640 docker/nginx/certs/HOST.privkey.pem
```

Renew: same mounts, `certbot/dns-cloudflare renew --cert-name HOST`, then recopy + reload nginx (`docker compose exec web nginx -s reload` on server).

## Deploy a single migration

```bash
rsync -az migrations/Users/mXXXX_....php bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl:/opt/freecrm/migrations/Users/
ssh bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl 'cd /opt/freecrm && docker compose exec -T app php yii migrate --migrationPath=migrations/Users/ --interactive=0'
```

Full source sync: `scripts/sync-freecrm.sh pushsrc`.

**Agent policy:** never run `pushsrc` automatically — ask the user first, then deploy only after explicit approval.

If the migration touches `yetiforce_menu`, regen menu cache on the server after migrate (see `settings-menu-icons.mdc` — `refreshMenuFiles()` inside migrate is unreliable).
